    <stitle>8 SPEED, 9 SPEED, AND 13 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON SERIES - REMOVE - CLUTCH HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>CLUTCH HOUSING</title>
        <specpara>
            <note>
                <para>For models so equipped, remove the clutch release mechanism and/or clutch brake assembly.</para>
            </note>
        </specpara>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the four bolts, and x nuts and lockwashers from the studs that secure the clutch
                housing to the transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301842">Figure 42</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301842" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301842" filename="../figg13/G1301842.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 42. Remove Bolts, Nuts and Lockwasher From Studs Securing Clutch Housing to Transmission
                    Case
                </caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Jar the clutch housing with a rubber mallet to break the gasket seal and pull from the
                transmission case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301843">Figure 43</hotlnk>). Remove the gasket.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301843" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301843" filename="../figg13/G1301843.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 43. Pull Clutch Housing From Transmission Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
